race.comment: STRAWBERRY IMPACT (9) at his peak for this and no excuses out to the mile. Sat off the good tempo and vigorously ridden in the straight when a sound second over 1500m at Randwick in BM78 class. Can race a little closer here and prove hard to hold out. DIAMOND SHOW (7) underrated mare who returned in good order when a slick winner with the 61kg over 1400m at Hawkesbury with something in hand. Will keep improving as she gets out in trip and Schiller sticks. Hard to get past. PRINCE OF SORTS (2) has a good record here and strips fitter after producing a respectable eighth over 1500m at Randwick in the Four Pillars. Winkers go on and has a key jockey change. MAGICON (6) races best with his runs spaced and has the ability to win this from the good draw. Kept up to the mark with a 1000m trial placing at Wyong. Looks the value play. GENERAL SOHO (4) tough gelding who saves his best for this track. Place best.
